java6035.tools.CLI
Class CLI

java.lang.Object
  java6035.tools.CLI.CLI

public class CLI
extends java.lang.Object

A generic command-line interface for 6.035 compilers. This class provides command-line parsing for student projects. It recognizes the required -target, -debug, -opt, and -o switches, and generates a name for input and output files.

Author:
6.035 Staff (6.035-staff@mit.edu)

Method Detail

parse

public static void parse(java.lang.String[] args,
                         java.lang.String[] optnames)
Parse the command-line arguments. Sets all of the result fields accordingly.
-target target sets the CLI.target field based on the target specified.
scan or scanner specifies CLI.SCAN parse specifies CLI.PARSE inter specifies CLI.INTER lowir specifies CLI.LOWIR assembly or codegen specifies CLI.ASSEMBLY The boolean array opts[] indicates which, if any, of the optimizations in optnames[] should be performed; these arrays are in the same order.

Parameters:
args - Array of arguments passed in to the program's Main function.
optnames - Ordered array of recognized optimization names.
